Exercise 14.4: Explain how to decide whether the following should be class
members:
(a) %  --> Should not be class member because it is a Symmetric operator.
(b) %= --> Should be class member because changing the state of the object.
(c) ++ --> Should be class member since it is changing the state of the object.
(d) -> --> Must be class member.
(e) << --> Should not be class member but friend function.
(f) && --> Should not be class member because it is a Symmetric operator.
(g) == --> Should not be class member because it is a Symmetric operator.
(h) () --> Must be class member.